# how to run the code

1. clone the repo from github
   git clone "https://github.com/Shubhptl/csbc1030.git"

2. cd csbc1030

3. open sql command line and add sql query for first user to log-in 
INSERT INTO User (name, username, password, email, phone, website)
VALUES ('Leanne Graham', 'Bret', 'Bret', 'Sincere@april.biz', '1-770-736-8031 x56442', 'hildegard.org');



# install all the dependencies and run the code

4. npm install sequelize mysql2
   npm install jsonwebtoken
   npm install cookie-parser
   npm install bcrypt
   


5. npm start

6. go to postman and select Post requerst and add follwing body
   http://localhost:3000/users/login
{
    
        "email": "Sincere@april.biz",
        "password":"Bret"
        
    }

7. Open the following url in browser for get('/') - ALL Post
http://localhost:3000/users to view all the users

8. Open the following url in browser for get('/') - All Users 
   http://localhost:3000/posts/1

9. Open the following url in browser for post('/') - Create Post
   http://localhost:3000/posts
  {
        "title": "sunt aut facere repellat provident occaecati excepturi optio reprehenderit",
        "body": "quia et suscipit\nsuscipit recusandae consequuntur expedita et cum\nreprehenderit molestiae ut ut quas totam\nnostrum rerum est autem sunt rem eveniet architecto"
    }

10. Open the following url in browser for patch('/:id') - Update Post
   http://localhost:3000/posts/1

{
        "title": "sunt aut facere repellat provident occaecati excepturi optio reprehenderit",
        "body": "test for comment"
    }
11. Open the following url in browser for get('/:postId/comment/:commentId') - ALL Comments for a particular Post
   http://localhost:3000/posts/1/comment

12. Open the following url in browser for post('/:postId/comment') - Create Comment for a particular Post
http://localhost:3000/posts/1/comment
{

        "body": "laudantium enim quasi est quidem magnam voluptate ipsam eos\ntempora quo necessitatibus\ndolor quam autem quasi\nreiciendis et nam sapiente accusantium"
    }

13. Open the following url in browser for patch('/:postId/comment/:commentId') - Update one Comment for a particular Post
http://localhost:3000/posts/1/comment/1
{

        "body": "laudantium enim quasi est quidem magnam voluptate ipsam eos\ntempora quo necessitatibus\ndolor quam autem quasi\nreiciendis et nam sapiente accusantium"
    }
    
14. Open the following url in browser for delete('/:postId/comments/:commentId') - Delete one Comment for a particular Post
http://localhost:3000/posts/1/comment/1 

# For Unit Testing and e2e Testing

npm run test

